INSERT INTO `june_11_2013_posts` VALUES (8,1,'2013-06-11 19:47:11','2013-06-11 19:47:11','<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Emergency food and clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</li>\r\n	<li>Food boxes distributed monthly</li>\r\n	<li>Commodities Distribution every fourth Wednesday of the month</li>\r\n	<li>Serenity Group (Faith Based Recovery Group)</li>\r\n	<li>Divine Appointment every Monday NigJht starting at 7pm (Worship, testimony, scripture and prayer)</li>\r\n	<li>Men\'s Ministry meeting every Thursday Night starting at 6:30pm</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the ACADC Counselors Institute (Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselors), a licensed class that prepares individuals to sit for the State Exam and obtain their State of California Alcohol/Drug Counselors license.</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition which provides housing solutions to those who are without shelter</li>\r\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><i>thank you all for coming out last night and supporting the Hope Center!  Together, we can make a difference! </i></p>\r\nhttps://vimeo.com/129778684\r\n\r\n<em><strong>          <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"> A huge thank you to our sponsors!!</span></strong></em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Oroville Safe &amp; Lock  534-0950</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Lynnrich (Taco Bell)  <span class=\"Apple-style-span\">534-1020</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">C J &amp; Pei Jan Shieh</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Robert &amp; Patricia Bateman (Roplast)  5895152</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\">Feather Falls Casino  533-3885  (Mark Grover)</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center;\"></div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\">Please help us partner with the Jordan Crossing ministry to make the first annual Color it Done Fun Run a success.  For more details or to visit their website, click the flier below.</div>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.jordancrossingministries.us/#!events-news/c1lr1\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-475\" src=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/production/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/53a1c9_ba18f80a4f2e49e1b2a0d2b645677ca4.jpg_srb_p_975_1469_75_22_0.50_1.20_0.00_jpg_srb-e1434457914974.jpg\" alt=\"53a1c9_ba18f80a4f2e49e1b2a0d2b645677ca4.jpg_srb_p_975_1469_75_22_0.50_1.20_0.00_jpg_srb\" width=\"400\" height=\"603\" /></a></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: left;\"></div>','Welcome to the Hope Center','','publish','open','open','','welcome','','','2015-06-16 05:44:01','2015-06-16 12:44:01','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?page_id=8',0,'page','',0),(10,1,'2013-06-11 19:48:00','2013-06-12 02:48:00','<h3>Our organization depends almost entirely on the grace of volunteers. Find ways to give hope to the hopeless.</h3>\r\nVolunteer for\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Operation Hope</li>\r\n	<li>Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</li>\r\n	<li>Work training partnerships</li>\r\n	<li>Special events</li>\r\n	<li>City Quest</li>\r\n	<li>Life Academy</li>\r\n	<li>Survival Services</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<a name=\"services\"></a>\r\n\r\nFill out the form below to get more information about how you can serve. Thank you for your generosity!\r\n[contact_form]\r\n\r\nYou may also call the Hope Center at 530.538.8398 to discuss service opportunities.','Serve','','publish','closed','closed','','serve','','','2014-11-08 12:30:05','2014-11-08 19:30:05','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?page_id=10',0,'page','',0),(11,1,'2013-06-11 19:48:18','2013-06-12 02:48:18','We cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nSupport the Hope Center\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</li>\r\n	<li>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</li>\r\n	<li>Donate securely online via PayPal with any major credit card (no PayPal account required)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\"><a href=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-118 size-full\" src=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/production/wp-content/uploads/2013/06/monthly-button.jpg\" alt=\"Donate Monthly\" width=\"107\" height=\"48\" /></a>                        <input alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donateCC_LG.gif\" type=\"image\" /></form><img src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" />\r\n\r\nThe Hope Center has been privileged to have a steady and growing base of private financial supporters. These include local citizens who understand and appreciate the mission and ministry of The Hope Center, as well as local businesses and churches longing to see lasting and impactive change in the Oroville Area. Once we moved into our new facility, our expenses almost tripled. Thankfully, as we have grown, our support base has grown. But there is still room for increase, as we are almost barely able to meet all of the necessary expenses.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Give','','publish','closed','closed','','give','','','2014-11-08 12:30:33','2014-11-08 19:30:33','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?page_id=11',0,'page','',0),(12,1,'2013-06-11 19:48:59','2013-06-11 19:48:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','12','','','2015-04-02 17:56:32','2015-04-03 00:56:32','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?p=12',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(13,1,'2013-06-11 19:48:59','2013-06-11 19:48:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','13','','','2015-04-02 17:56:32','2015-04-03 00:56:32','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?p=13',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(14,1,'2013-06-11 19:48:59','2013-06-11 19:48:59',' ','','','publish','open','open','','14','','','2015-04-02 17:56:32','2015-04-03 00:56:32','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?p=14',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(15,1,'2013-06-11 19:47:11','2013-06-11 19:47:11','','Learn','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2013-06-11 19:47:11','2013-06-11 19:47:11','',8,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(16,1,'2013-06-11 20:28:06','2013-06-11 20:28:06','','Welcome to the Hope Center','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2013-06-11 20:28:06','2013-06-11 20:28:06','',8,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),(17,1,'2013-06-11 20:28:55','2013-06-11 20:28:55','','Welcome to the Hope Center','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2013-06-11 20:28:55','2013-06-11 20:28:55','',8,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),(19,1,'2013-06-11 20:33:52','2013-06-11 20:33:52','<div class=\"intro-box group\">\r\n\r\n<span class=\"heading\">Learn</span>\r\n<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities.</h3>\r\n<a class=\"more\" href=\"#services\">Learn more\r\n&amp; get help ↓</a>\r\n\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"events\"><span class=\"subheading\">Upcoming Events</span>\r\n[google-calendar-events type=\"list\" max=\"10\"]</div>\r\n<div id=\"services\"><a name=\"services\"></a>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>A Simple Gesture</h3>\r\nWe drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to food banks around Oroville. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need? Click for more info and to sign up!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Operation Hope - Food Ministry</h3>\r\nThe Operation Hope team meets at 6 AM on Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday mornings to prepare and package a fresh hot breakfast for those who are hungry. The breakfast is then served at local parks in Downtown Oroville. In addition, a hot lunch is served on Fridays at The Hope Center. Everyone is welcome.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Clothing Assistance</h3>\r\nOur warehouse contains organized racks of like-new clothing that are completely FREE to anyone in need.  Clients may take:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>3 bottoms</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>4 tops</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 jacket</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 coat in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>2 miscellaneous items (such as shoes, underwear, belts, etc.)</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 pajama set</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 sheet set</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>1 blanket in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Businesswear/suits available in addition to regular allowances for interviews, court, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOccasionally furniture, toiletries, hygiene products and household linens are available as well.  Clients can return once every two months for more clothing assistance, or if homeless, once every month.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Day Use Center</h3>\r\nAt The Hope Center, a wet-weather, drop-in, day-use center is currently under construction. We currently serve hot meals and fellowship with the needy and homeless in our main warehouse that has a makeshift dining area and houses our Community Kitchen Trailer. We offer laundry services to homeless only Tuesday through Friday from 10am to 1pm. Showers available Tuesday through Thursday 9am to 1pm, and 11am to 1pm on Fridays.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Life Skills Academy (LSA)</h3>\r\nLife Skills Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, local government agencies, and churches to provide free basic life skills education in order to effect a positive change in peoples\' lives, helping them to contribute to the community, creating a better environment for individuals, businesses and law enforcement personnel, and even saving tax-payer dollars.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Welcome to the Hope Center','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2013-06-11 20:33:52','2013-06-11 20:33:52','',8,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/8-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2013-06-11 21:06:59','2013-06-11 21:06:59','We drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to the Hope Center Food Bank.  The food is then broken down into food boxes for families/individuals in our community. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need?  We believe that Oroville can take care of it\'s own!  Click for more info and to sign up','A Simple Gesture','','publish','closed','closed','','a-simple-gesture','','','2013-07-18 18:28:25','2013-07-18 18:28:25','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?post_type=services&#038;p=20',0,'services','',0),(22,2,'2013-07-18 18:27:39','2013-07-18 18:27:39','We drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to the Hope Center Food Bank.  The food is then broken down into food boxes for families/individuals in our community. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need?  We believe that Oroville can take care of it\'s own!  Click for more info and to sign up','A Simple Gesture','','inherit','open','open','','20-autosave','','','2013-07-18 18:27:39','2013-07-18 18:27:39','',20,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/20-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(23,1,'2013-06-11 21:16:00','2013-06-11 21:16:00','The Operation Hope team feeds a Hot Meal Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday 10am to 11:30am.  On Friday, Oroville Faith Center provides sack lunches from 10 am to 11:30 am.  On Saturday mornings the Christian Faith Center Team feeds a Hot Meal from 9:30 am to 11 am.  On Sunday The Fathers House and the Op Hope Team join together and provide Sunday Supper Service from 4 pm to  5:30 pm.  Everyone is welcome.  Meals are served at The Hope Center, 1950 Kitrick Ave.','Operation Hope - Food Ministry','','publish','closed','closed','','operation-hope-food-ministry','','','2014-10-21 22:45:19','2014-10-21 22:45:19','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.dev/?post_type=services&#038;p=23',0,'services','',0),(25,1,'2013-06-11 21:16:52','2013-06-11 21:16:52','After initial assessment, a comprehensive strategy is developed to meet the basic needs of the individual or family. This may include any/all of the following: Emergency Food Bags, placement in our Food Box (A Simple Gesture) ministry, Clothing, personal hygiene items, furniture/household goods, providing collaborative in-house services such as; shelter (GOHC), and Addictions counselling (ACADC). The HC also acts as a “portal” to a host of City/County services. Spiritual guidance and prayer is always a priority when needed.\r\n\r\nOur warehouse contains organized racks of like-new clothing that are completely FREE to anyone in need.  Clients may take:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 bottoms</li>\r\n	<li>4 tops</li>\r\n	<li>1 jacket</li>\r\n	<li>1 coat in a 6 month period</li>\r\n	<li>2 miscellaneous items (such as shoes, underwear, be