 of the Hope Center I get people pulling from all different directions but I want to talk about two areas. Social Action and Evangelical efforts. Many people and organizations want me to be more socially/politically engaged while others want me to be more hard-lined while sharing the gospel. It seems that I can never satiate both, but at times I can satisfy one or the other or so it seems. It gets really confusing and to tell the truth sometimes I just want to find a place to withdraw and wait out the storm. When I find myself in these storms I know I can look to Jesus for inspiration. As much as I like pleasing people; pleasing Him is all that really matters.\r\nJesus didn’t hide…he so loved the world that he entered it. I mean can you for one minute imagine the Son of God leaving heaven to come hang out with us? It seems crazy to me. I have a hard time wrapping my head around that one! If I call myself a follower of Jesus how can I turn from the world and try to escape it when he asks (and leads by example) for us to love it? I can’t. He called me to “love my neighbor” and that compels me to get involved in the issues and politics that affect our community. He also called me to make Disciples and that requires a strong Biblical Foundation and is an Evangelical mandate.\r\nIn an organizational sense this is accomplished by us here at the Hope Center by being very active in the social justice role (loving our neighbor) and being able to plug people in to existing church bodies in an effort to ensure they receive the biblical foundation necessary (evangelical). This is also a beautiful display of the Body of Christ at work. Those that are called to Social Action/Justice and those that are called to Teaching/Preaching!\r\nOn a personal level I totally want to engage in social action while embracing the creation mandate to love all of the creation (the secular world). God has a desire for all of creation (life) not just religious aspects of it. God loves it when His people get together and worship but he has a longing for those who don’t. So, I will continue to study scripture and be Biblically sound while taking on the issues of our community head on in hopes of making Jesus famous!\r\nMartin Luther King: “Religion deals with both heaven and earth…Any religion that professes to be concerned with the souls of men and is not concerned with the slums that doom them, the economic conditions that strangle them, and the social conditions that cripple them, is a dry-as-dust religion.”\r\nRecommend Read: “Balanced Christianity” by John Stott, Intervarsity Press\r\nIf you have a desire to partner with us please go to www.orovillehopecenter.org and hit the “Give” tab.\r\nBlessings','Beauty in Balance','','publish','open','open','','55','','','2014-07-16 23:09:31','2014-07-16 23:09:31','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=55',0,'post','',0),(59,2,'2014-07-16 21:00:09','2014-07-16 21:00:09','Beauty in Balance\r\nSometimes I struggle trying to walk out my faith in today’s world.  It’s not easy to be an example of Jesus to others in today’s culture.  As the Director of the Hope Center I get people pulling from all different directions but I want to talk about two areas.  Social Action and Evangelical efforts.  Many people and organizations want me to be more socially/politically engaged while others want me to be more hard-lined while sharing the gospel.  It seems that I can never satiate both, but at times I can satisfy one or the other or so it seems.  It gets really confusing and to tell the truth sometimes I just want to find a place to withdraw and wait out the storm.  When I find myself in these storms I know I can look to Jesus for inspiration.  As much as I like pleasing people; pleasing Him is all that really matters.  \r\nJesus didn’t hide…he so loved the world that he entered it.  I mean can you for one minute imagine the Son of God leaving heaven to come hang out with us?  It seems crazy to me.  I have a hard time wrapping my head around that one!  If I call myself a follower of Jesus how can I turn from the world and try to escape it when he asks (and leads by example) for us to love it?  I can’t.  He called me to “love my neighbor” and that compels me to get involved in the issues and politics that affect our community.  He also called me to make Disciples and that requires a strong Biblical Foundation and is an Evangelical mandate. \r\nIn an organizational sense this is accomplished by us here at the Hope Center by being very active in the social justice role (loving our neighbor) and being able to plug people in to existing church bodies in an effort to ensure they receive the biblical foundation necessary (evangelical).  This is also a beautiful display of the Body of Christ at work.  Those that are called to Social Action/Justice and those that are called to Teaching/Preaching!\r\nOn a personal level I totally want to engage in social action while embracing the creation mandate to love all of the creation (the secular world).  God has a desire for all of creation (life) not just religious aspects of it.  God loves it when His people get together and worship but he has a longing for those who don’t.  So, I will continue to study scripture and be Biblically sound while taking on the issues of our community head on in hopes of making Jesus famous!\r\nMartin Luther King:  “Religion deals with both heaven and earth…Any religion that professes to be concerned with the souls of men and is not concerned with the slums that doom them, the economic conditions that strangle them, and the social conditions that cripple them, is a dry-as-dust religion.”\r\nRecommend Read:  “Balanced Christianity” by John Stott, Intervarsity Press\r\nIf you have a desire to partner with us please go to www.orovillehopecenter.org and hit the “Give” tab.\r\nBlessings\r\n','','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision','','','2014-07-16 21:00:09','2014-07-16 21:00:09','',55,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/55-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(61,2,'2015-04-02 17:24:52','2015-04-03 00:24:52','','Events','','publish','open','open','','events','','','2015-04-02 17:26:10','2015-04-03 00:26:10','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?page_id=61',0,'page','',0),(62,2,'2014-07-21 01:57:56','2014-07-21 01:57:56','<iframe src=\"http://www.google.com/calendar/embed?src=orovillehopecenter.org_7nmf5uv2brbpmig7v192nflu8k%40group.calendar.google.com&ctz=America/Los_Angeles\" style=\"border: 0\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" frameborder=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"></iframe>','','','inherit','open','open','','61-revision-v1','','','2014-07-21 01:57:56','2014-07-21 01:57:56','',61,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/61-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(64,1,'2013-06-11 21:54:34','2013-06-11 21:54:34','<h3>We cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.</h3>\r\nSupport the Hope Center\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</span></li>\r\n	<li><span>Donate securely online via PayPal with any major credit card (no PayPal account required)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<form action=\"https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr\" method=\"post\"><input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cmd\" value=\"_s-xclick\" />\r\n<input type=\"hidden\" name=\"hosted_button_id\" value=\"BEYXHT8VC9N3Y\" />\r\n<input type=\"image\" alt=\"PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!\" name=\"submit\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donateCC_LG.gif\" />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif\" width=\"1\" height=\"1\" border=\"0\" /></form>Hayden Ministries has been privileged to have a steady and growing base of private financial supporters. These include local citizens who understand and appreciate the mission and ministry of The Hope Center, as well as local businesses and churches longing to see lastin