//orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>','Danny\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','206-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 03:07:19','2014-10-26 03:07:19','',206,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/206-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(214,2,'2014-10-30 05:30:18','2014-10-30 05:30:18','<br></br>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">   </span>After serving 18 years in the State Penitentiary, I was released in Oroville and went to the Hope Center.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>While there, they provided me with basic survival services; clothes and food, but also the staff showed me kindness, courtesy, respect and most of all, the love of Jesus.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I began a journey of discipleship class, connected with a local church and I was able to get a job.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I led the Parolee Process Group, got married and began to be contributing member of society and a provider for my family.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am a husband, a father and a man after God’s heart.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Life Academy</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Life Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, the ACADC Institute, local agencies, and churches to provide free basic life education in order to effect a positive change in peoples’ lives. This helps them to contribute to the community, creates a better environment for individuals, businesses, and law enforcement personnel. It even saves tax-payer dollars.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]The Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselor’s Institute (ACADC) is housed in the Hope Center. Their purpose is to train and certify Drug, Alcohol &amp; Addictions Counselors in accordance with Biblical Christian principles.[/box]','Chuck\'s Story','','publish','closed','closed','','chucks-story','','http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\nhttp://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\nhttp://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/','2014-10-30 22:55:05','2014-10-31 05:55:05','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=214',0,'post','',0),(215,2,'2014-10-26 03:11:18','2014-10-26 03:11:18','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">   </span>After serving 18 years in the State Penitentiary, I was released in Oroville and went to the Hope Center.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>While there, they provided me with basic survival services; clothes and food, but also the staff showed me kindness, courtesy, respect and most of all, the love of Jesus.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I began a journey of discipleship class, connected with a local church and I was able to get a job.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I led the Parolee Process Group, got married and began to be contributing member of society and a provider for my family.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am a husband, a father and a man after God’s heart.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Life Academy</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Life Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, the ACADC Institute, local agencies, and churches to provide free basic life education in order to effect a positive change in peoples’ lives. This helps them to contribute to the community, creates a better environment for individuals, businesses, and law enforcement personnel. It even saves tax-payer dollars.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"# http://orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>','Chuck\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','214-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 03:11:18','2014-10-26 03:11:18','',214,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/214-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(216,2,'2014-10-31 05:30:44','2014-10-31 05:30:44','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span>Three and a half years ago I was heavy into my addiction into drugs and alcohol.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>At least one year of that time I was homeless.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>No matter how lost, lonely or how hard it was to love myself for what I was going through, I knew that I could come to the Hope Center and receive not just basic needs, but also kindness and caring.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I found hope and what I could have back in my life.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am now clean and sober for a year and a half.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am currently serving community service and chose to give back to the one place that gave back to me.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Survival Services</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Meets the most basic/stabilizing needs such as; food, clothing, personal hygiene items, sleeping bags, furniture, collaborative services (i.e. shelter, counseling), prayer and spiritual guidance<span class=\"s1\">.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Mont