nter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"# http://orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>','Dawn\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','216-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 03:18:09','2014-10-26 03:18:09','',216,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/216-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(220,2,'2014-11-01 05:30:36','2014-11-01 05:30:36','<br></br>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  My name is Jill and I love Jesus Christ! <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>A year ago I would have never proclaimed this.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>My recovery began in 2005, but really it wasn’t until I contacted a close friend and believer needing direction and guidance.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>It was then that I made a leap of faith towards a fulfilling relationship with Jesus.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Amazing things were changing; I was changing and was letting God direct my life.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On March 11, 2014 I drove to the Hope Center for the first time to start the ACADC classes and to volunteer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>All I can say is “WOW”.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I have learned so much about the Word of God, strength and power of scripture, love, kindness and unity.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I daily give praise for the Hope Center and ACADC classes for my relationship with the Lord and that my recovery in on firm ground.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>ACADC Institute</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Housed in the Hope Center, ACADC (Association of Christian Alcohol &amp; Drug Counselors) provides training for individuals to become State of California Registered Addiction Specialist’s.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>This Ministry also provides on-site addictions counseling and referrals to recovery homes/residential programs.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<hr />\r\n[box]God has used the HC to create 7 part-time jobs.  The Director is the lowest paid employee of the 7.[/box]','Jill\'s Story','','publish','closed','closed','','jills-story','','\nhttp://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/','2014-11-01 22:31:20','2014-11-02 05:31:20','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=220',0,'post','',0),(221,2,'2014-10-26 03:24:24','2014-10-26 03:24:24','<p class=\"p1\">  My name is Jill and I love Jesus Christ! <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>A year ago I would have never proclaimed this.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>My recovery began in 2005, but really it wasn’t until I contacted a close friend and believer needing direction and guidance.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>It was then that I made a leap of faith towards a fulfilling relationship with Jesus.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Amazing things were changing; I was changing and was letting God direct my life.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On March 11, 2014 I drove to the Hope Center for the first time to start the ACADC classes and to volunteer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>All I can say is “WOW”.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I have learned so much about the Word of God, strength and power of scripture, love, kindness and unity.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I daily give praise for the Hope Center and ACADC classes for my relationship with the Lord and that my recovery in on firm ground.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>ACADC Institute</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Housed in the Hope Center, ACADC (Association of Christian Alcohol &amp; Drug Counselors) provides training for individuals to become State of California Registered Addiction Specialist’s.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>This Ministry also provides on-site addictions counseling and referrals to recovery homes/residential programs.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"# http://orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>','Jill\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','220-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 03:24:24','2014-10-26 03:24:24','',220,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/220-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(222,2,'2014-11-02 05:30:29','2014-11-02 05:30:29','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  Today I choose to stay in the solution and not the problem.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center clearly provides me a living example of where I could very easily end up in less fortunate circumstances should I choose to pick up another drink.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Like they say in the program, “I may have another drink left in me, but I just may not have another recovery.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center is a definite part of my solution.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In serving others, I can show that there is indeed a way out of the nightmare that is addiction.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]Did you know that if you do not have the ability to give monthly we can send you a shares card for Food Maxx. It won’t cost you anything and if you swipe it when buying groceries Food Maxx will donate 3% of your total purchase to the HC?[/box]','Henry\'s Story','','publish','closed','closed','','henrys-story','','\nhttp://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/','2014-11-02 22:44:48','2014-11-03 05:44:48','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=222',0,'post','',0),(223,2,'2014-10-26 03:38:16','2014-10-26 03:38:16','<p class=\"p1\">  Today I choose to stay in the solution and not the problem.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center clearly provides me a living example of where I could very easily end up in less fortunate circumstances should I choose to pick up another drink.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Like they say in the program, “I may have another drink left in me, but I just may not have another recovery.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center is a definite part of my solution.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In serving others, I can show that there is indeed a way out of the nightmare that is addiction.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"# http://orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>','Henry\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','222-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 03:38:16','2014-10-26 03:38:16','',222,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/222-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(224,2,'2014-10-26 03:45:35','2014-10-26 03:45:35','<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\"><b>WELCOME</b></span> to S.H.A.R.E.S., our fund-raising program offered free to more than 8,500 schools, groups and organizations by Save Mart and our affiliated stores (Lucky Supermarkets, FoodMaxx and S-Mart Foods). Each year, we set aside a reserve of $4.5 million specifically to benefit those who have enrolled in S.H.A.R.E.S.  <span class=\"s2\">S.H.A.R.E.S. is an acronym for Supporting Humanities, Arts, Recreation, Education and Sports, and it is Save Mart’s way of giving back to the communities we call home.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">By swiping a Hope Center SHARES card when you shop at Food Maxx or other participating supermarket, a percentage of your purchase (that is NOT in addition to your purchase) is donated quarterly to The Hope Center.  If you would like to receive a S.H.A.R.E.S. Card in the mail, leave your name and address and we will send you one.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">[formidable id=3 title=true]</p>','S.H.A.R.E.S. Program','','inherit','open','open','','195-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 03:45:35','2014-10-26 03:45:35','',195,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/195-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(225,2,'2014-11-03 05:30:14','2014-11-03 05:30:14','<br></br>\r\nTodd was living in an orchard, struggling with a serious alcohol addiction, sometimes drinking a gallon or more of whiskey a day. One day someone told him about The Hope Center, so he came here asking for help. He was connected with Catherine Sparrow of the ACADC, then after “one last drink” he returned in tears and signed on with Lifeline Recovery Ministries.  Todd is now 64 days clean and has become the Maintenance Manager for Lifeline. Todd feels so blessed to have had a life changing experience with Jesus thanks to ACADC, The Hope Center and Lifeline Recovery Ministry.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n<br></br>\