 Card[/button]</p>','Todd\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','225-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 15:55:42','2014-10-26 15:55:42','',225,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/225-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(228,2,'2014-11-04 05:30:42','2014-11-04 05:30:42','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  I have lived between homes for about 30 years after I destroyed my family with addiction.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I came to the Hope Center for the hot meals.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>One day as I was eating, I sat at a table with a couple younger men,<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>As I was listening to them talk, one of them asked me how old I was.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I told him and he replied that his Dad was about my age and that he hadn’t seen him in about 30 years.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We came to realize that I was his father!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We had been passing each other on the streets of Oroville many times.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We are united now and living together!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Operation Hope</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Operation Hope team feeds a Hot Meal Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday 10am to 11:30am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On Friday, Oroville Faith Center provides sack lunches from 10 am to 11:30 am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On Saturday mornings the Christian Faith Center Team feeds a Hot Meal from 9:30 am to 11 am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On Sunday the Fathers House provides Sunday Supper Service from 4 pm to 5:30 pm.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Everyone is welcome.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Meals are served at The Hope Center, 1950 Kitrick Ave.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]God through the HC, serves up on average 1,886 meals a month. For .69 cents you can feed a person a hot meal at the HC. For $25 per month you can sponsor 36 meals.[/box]\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>','Dan\'s Story','','publish','closed','closed','','dans-story','','','2014-11-04 22:27:08','2014-11-05 05:27:08','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=228',0,'post','',0),(229,2,'2014-10-26 15:58:44','2014-10-26 15:58:44','<p class=\"p1\">  I have lived between homes for about 30 years after I destroyed my family with addiction.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I came to the Hope Center for the hot meals.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>One day as I was eating, I sat at a table with a couple younger men,<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>As I was listening to them talk, one of them asked me how old I was.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I told him and he replied that his Dad was about my age and that he hadn’t seen him in about 30 years.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We came to realize that I was his father!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We had been passing each other on the streets of Oroville many times.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We are united now and living together!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Operation Hope</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Operation Hope team feeds a Hot Meal Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday 10am to 11:30am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On Friday, Oroville Faith Center provides sack lunches from 10 am to 11:30 am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-spac