 those who are without shelter</li>\r\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n[google-calendar-events]','Welcome to the Hope Center','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 16:13:24','2014-10-26 16:13:24','',8,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(231,2,'2014-10-26 16:22:17','2014-10-26 16:22:17','<h3 class=\"intro\">We are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities</h3>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Emergency food and clothing</li>\r\n	<li>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</li>\r\n	<li>Food boxes distributed monthly</li>\r\n	<li>Commodities Distribution every fourth Wednesday of the month</li>\r\n	<li>Serenity Group (Faith Based Recovery Group)</li>\r\n	<li>Divine Appointment every Monday Night starting at 7pm (Worship, testimony, scripture and prayer)</li>\r\n	<li>Men\'s Ministry meeting every Thursday Night starting at 6:30pm</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the ACADC Counselors Institute (Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselors), a licensed class that prepares individuals to sit for the State Exam and obtain their State of California Alcohol/Drug Counselors license.</li>\r\n	<li>Home of the Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition which provides housing solutions to those who are without shelter</li>\r\n	<li>In partnership with Starting Over Strong; expungement classes are offered bi-monthly</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n&nbsp;','Welcome to the Hope Center','','inherit','open','open','','8-revision-v1','','','2014-10-26 16:22:17','2014-10-26 16:22:17','',8,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/8-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(232,2,'2014-11-05 05:30:47','2014-11-05 05:30:47','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  I had been attending the Serenity Recovery Group at the Nazarene church still struggling with my addiction until I learned I was pregnant.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>A year after my son was born, the City Quest Ministry came to my apartment complex giving out food and prayer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>After an accident I was in, I began to go to church with the City Quest team.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>My boyfriend and I are now attending church together and we have plans on getting married soon with the City Quest team officiating!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>City Quest</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Where saints from different organizations gather to be the hands and feet of Jesus and reach-out to those who live in apartment complexes and other isolated conditions...we meet needs and minister to those who would not normally make it to the Center.  Come join us!  Meet in the HC Food Bank Parking Lot on Thursday\'s at 3:30pm...Blessings</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]God through the HC distributes food to over 30 organizations throughout our City and Butte County. Last year God through the HC distributed a total of 284,742 lbs of food to individuals, families and organizations in need.[/box]','Toba\'s Story','','publish','closed','closed','','tobas-story','','http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\nhttp://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/','2014-11-05 22:47:16','2014-11-06 05:47:16','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=232',0,'post','',0),(233,2,'2014-10-27 00:46:55','2014-10-27 00:46:55','<p class=\"p1\">  I had been attending the Serenity Recovery Group at the Nazarene church still struggling with my addiction until I learned I was pregnant.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>A year after my son was born, the City Quest Ministry came to my apartment complex giving out food and prayer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>After an accident I was in, I began to go to church with the City Quest team.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>My boyfriend and I are now attending church together and we have plans on getting married soon with the City Quest team officiating!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>City Quest</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Where saints from different organizations gather to be the hands and feet of Jesus and reach-out to those who live in apartment complexes and other isolated conditions...we meet needs and minister to those who would not normally make it to the Center.  Come join us!  Meet in the HC Food Bank Parking Lot on Thursday\'s at 3:30pm...Blessings</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"# http://orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>','Toba\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','232-revision-v1','','','2014-10-27 00:46:55','2014-10-27 00:46:55','',232,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/232-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(235,2,'2014-11-06 05:30:56','2014-11-06 05:30:56','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  Through Work Experience I chose to work at the Hope Center based on my personal experience.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center helped my family when we were in need and I was able to see the impact that just a small amount of help could do.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Now that I am here, I am proud to be a part of such an honest, helpful and caring organization.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Every day it is a privilege to really help people and there is no better use of my time.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><i>Service Opportunities</i></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[box] The total number of people/organizations that give monthly to the HC average about 40 per month at approximately $225.00 per month. Of the 40 per month givers; two are faith based organizations (churches).[/box]</p>','Haley\'s Story','','publish','closed','closed','','haleys-story','','\nhttp://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/','2014-11-06 22:25:38','2014-11-07 05:25:38','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=235',0,'post','',0),(236,2,'2014-10-27 01:00:11','2014-10-27 01:00:11','<p class=\"p1\">  Through Work Experience I chose to work at the Hope Center based on my personal experience.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center helped my family when we were in need and I was able to see the impact that just a small amount of help could do.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>No