d-space\">   </span>After serving 18 years in the State Penitentiary, I was released in Oroville and went to the Hope Center.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>While there, they provided me with basic survival services; clothes and food, but also the staff showed me kindness, courtesy, respect and most of all, the love of Jesus.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I began a journey of discipleship class, connected with a local church and I was able to get a job.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I led the Parolee Process Group, got married and began to be contributing member of society and a provider for my family.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am a husband, a father and a man after God’s heart.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Life Academy</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Life Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, the ACADC Institute, local agencies, and churches to provide free basic life education in order to effect a positive change in peoples’ lives. This helps them to contribute to the community, creates a better environment for individuals, businesses, and law enforcement personnel. It even saves tax-payer dollars.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]The Association of Christian Alcohol and Drug Counselor’s Institute (ACADC) is housed in the Hope Center. Their purpose is to train and certify Drug, Alcohol &amp; Addictions Counselors in accordance with Biblical Christian principles.[/box]','Chuck\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','214-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:20:14','2014-10-28 03:20:14','',214,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/214-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(275,2,'2014-10-28 03:24:27','2014-10-28 03:24:27','<br></br>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span>Three and a half years ago I was heavy into my addiction into drugs and alcohol.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>At least one year of that time I was homeless.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>No matter how lost, lonely or how hard it was to love myself for what I was going through, I knew that I could come to the Hope Center and receive not just basic needs, but also kindness and caring.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I found hope and what I could have back in my life.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am now clean and sober for a year and a half.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am currently serving community service and chose to give back to the one place that gave back to me.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Survival Services</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Meets the most basic/stabilizing needs such as; food, clothing, personal hygiene items, sleeping bags, furniture, collaborative services (i.e. shelter, counseling), prayer and spiritual guidance<span class=\"s1\">.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<hr />\r\n[box]God through the Hope Center, serves on average 3,395 guests per month. The Hope Center does not receive any grants and is supported fully by independent people/organizations.[/box]','Dawn\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','216-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:24:27','2014-10-28 03:24:27','',216,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/216-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(276,2,'2014-10-28 03:28:33','2014-10-28 03:28:33','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span>Three and a half years ago I was heavy into my addiction into drugs and alcohol.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>At least one year of that time I was homeless.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>No matter how lost, lonely or how hard it was to love myself for what I was going through, I knew that I could come to the Hope Center and receive not just basic needs, but also kindness and caring.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I found hope and what I could have back in my life.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am now clean and sober for a year and a half.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I am currently serving community service and chose to give back to the one place that gave back to me.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Survival Services</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Meets the most basic/stabilizing needs such as; food, clothing, personal hygiene items, sleeping bags, furniture, collaborative services (i.e. shelter, counseling), prayer and spiritual guidance<span class=\"s1\">.</span></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]God through the Hope Center, serves on average 3,395 guests per month. The Hope Center does not receive any grants and is supported fully by independent people/organizations.[/box]','Dawn\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','216-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:28:33','2014-10-28 03:28:33','',216,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/216-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(277,2,'2014-10-28 03:37:01','2014-10-28 03:37:01','<br></br>\n<p class=\"p1\">  My name is Jill and I love Jesus Christ! <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>A year ago I would have never proclaimed this.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>My recovery began in 2005, but really it wasn’t until I contacted a close friend and believer needing direction and guidance.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>It was then that I made a leap of faith towards a fulfilling relationship with Jesus.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Amazing things were changing; I was changing and was letting God direct my life.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On March 11, 2014 I drove to the Hope Center for the first time to start the ACADC classes and to volunteer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>All I can say is “WOW”.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I have learned so much about the Word of God, strength and power of scripture, love, kindness and unity.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I daily give praise for the Hope Center and ACADC classes for my relationship with the Lord and that my recovery in on firm ground.</p>\n&nbsp;\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>ACADC Institute</em></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">Housed in the Hope Center, ACADC (Association of Christian Alcohol &amp; Drug Counselors) provides training for individuals to become State of California Registered Addiction Specialist’s.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>This Ministry also provides on-site addictions counseling and referrals to recovery homes/residential programs.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<hr />\n\n&nbsp;\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\n<br></br>\n<hr />\n[box]God has used the HC to create 7 part-time jobs.  The Director is the lowest paid employee of the 7.[/box]','Jill\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','220-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:37:01','2014-10-28 03:37:01','',220,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/220-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(278,2,'2014-10-28 03:38:00','2014-10-28 03:38:00','<br></br>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  My name is Jill and I love Jesus Christ! <span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>A year ago I would have never proclaimed this.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>My recovery began in 2005, but really it wasn’t until I contacted a close friend and believer needing direction and guidance.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>It was then that I made a leap of faith towards a fulfilling relationship with Jesus.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Amazing things were changing; I was changing and was letting God direct my life.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On March 11, 2014 I drove to the Hope Center for the first time to start the ACADC classes and to volunteer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>All I can say is “WOW”.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I have learned so much about the Word of God, strength and power of scripture, love, kindness and unity.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I daily give praise for the Hope Center and ACADC classes for my relationship with the Lord and that my recovery in on firm ground.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>ACADC Institute</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Housed in the Hope Center, ACADC (Association of Christian Alcohol &amp; Drug Counselors) provides training for individuals to become State of California Registered Addiction Specialist’s.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>This Ministry also provides on-site addictions counseling and referrals to recovery homes/residential programs.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<hr />\r\n[box]God has used the HC to create 7 part-time jobs.  The Director is the lowest paid employee of the 7.[/box]','Jill\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','220-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:38:00','2014-10-28 03:38:00','',220,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/220-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(279,2,'2014-10-28 03:46:00','2014-10-28 03:46:00','<br></br>\n<p class=\"p1\">  Today I choose to stay in the solution and not the problem.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center clearly provides me a living example of where I could very easily end up in less fortunate circumstances should I choose to pick up another drink.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Like they say in the program, “I may have another drink left in me, but I just may not have another recovery.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center is a definite part of my solution.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In serving others, I can show that there is indeed a way out of the nightmare that is addiction.</p>\n&nbsp;\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<hr />\n\n&nbsp;\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"# http://orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\n<br></br>\n<hr />\n[box]','Henry\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','222-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:46:00','2014-10-28 03:46:00','',222,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/222-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(280,2,'2014-10-28 03:46:49','2014-10-28 03:46:49','<br></br>\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  Today I choose to stay in the solution and not the problem.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center clearly provides me a living example of where I could very easily end up in less fortunate circumstances should I choose to pick up another drink.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Like they say in the program, “I may have another drink left in me, but I just may not have another recovery.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center is a definite part of my solution.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In serving others, I can show that there is indeed a way out of the nightmare that is addiction.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"#http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"# http://orovillehopecenter.org/cant-help-now-pdf/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<hr />\r\n[box]Did you know that if you do not have the ability to give monthly we can send you a shares card for Food Maxx.  It won’t cost you anything and if you swipe it when buying groceries Food Maxx will donate 3% of your total purchase to the HC?[/box]','Henry\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','222-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:46:49','2014-10-28 03:46:49','',222,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/222-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(281,2,'2014-10-28 03:47:32','2014-10-28 03:47:32','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  Today I choose to stay in the solution and not the problem.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center clearly provides me a living example of where I could very easily end up in less fortunate circumstances should I choose to pick up another drink.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Like they say in the program, “I may have another drink left in me, but I just may not have another recovery.”<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center is a definite part of my solution.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>In serving others, I can show that there is indeed a way out of the nightmare that is addiction.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]Did you know that if you do not have the ability to give monthly we can send you a shares card for Food Maxx. It won’t cost you anything and if you swipe it when buying groceries Food Maxx will donate 3% of your total purchase to the HC?[/box]','Henry\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','222-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:47:32','2014-10-28 03:47:32','',222,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/222-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(282,2,'2014-10-28 03:55:17','2014-10-28 03:55:17','<br></br>\nTodd was living in an orchard, struggling with a serious alcohol addiction, sometimes drinking a gallon or more of whiskey a day. One day someone told him about The Hope Center, so he came here asking for help. He was connected with Catherine Sparrow of the ACADC, then after “one last drink” he returned in tears and signed on with Lifeline Recovery Ministries.  Todd is now 64 days clean and has become the Maintenance Manager for Lifeline. Todd feels so blessed to have had a life changing experience with Jesus thanks to ACADC, The Hope Center and Lifeline Recovery Ministry.\n\n&nbsp;\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<hr />\n\n&nbsp;\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\n<br></br>\n<hr />\n[box]The Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition (GOHC) is housed in the Hope Center.  They work to end homelessness one individual or family at a time by providing housing assistance.[/box]','Todd\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','225-autosave-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:55:17','2014-10-28 03:55:17','',225,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/225-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(283,2,'2014-10-28 03:56:37','2014-10-28 03:56:37','<br></br>\r\nTodd was living in an orchard, struggling with a serious alcohol addiction, sometimes drinking a gallon or more of whiskey a day. One day someone told him about The Hope Center, so he came here asking for help. He was connected with Catherine Sparrow of the ACADC, then after “one last drink” he returned in tears and signed on with Lifeline Recovery Ministries.  Todd is now 64 days clean and has become the Maintenance Manager for Lifeline. Todd feels so blessed to have had a life changing experience with Jesus thanks to ACADC, The Hope Center and Lifeline Recovery Ministry.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Service Opportunities</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Hope Center provides a place for people to engage our community by learning to serve others.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Avenues of service include:<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>The Hope Center Volunteer Program, Court appointed Community Service hours, Recovery Program Community Service hours and Butte County Employment Programs including Work Experience and CalWorks/TANF as well as Section 8 service hours.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n<br></br>\r\n<hr />\r\n[box]The Greater Oroville Homeless Coalition (GOHC) is housed in the Hope Center.  They work to end homelessness one individual or family at a time by providing housing assistance.[/box]','Todd\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','225-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:56:37','2014-10-28 03:56:37','',225,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/225-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(284,2,'2014-10-28 03:58:43','2014-10-28 03:58:43','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  I have lived between homes for about 30 years after I destroyed my family with addiction.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I came to the Hope Center for the hot meals.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>One day as I was eating, I sat at a table with a couple younger men,<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>As I was listening to them talk, one of them asked me how old I was.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I told him and he replied that his Dad was about my age and that he hadn’t seen him in about 30 years.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We came to realize that I was his father!<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We had been passing each other on the streets of Oroville many times.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>We are united now and living together!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>Operation Hope</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">The Operation Hope team feeds a Hot Meal Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday 10am to 11:30am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On Friday, Oroville Faith Center provides sack lunches from 10 am to 11:30 am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On Saturday mornings the Christian Faith Center Team feeds a Hot Meal from 9:30 am to 11 am.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>On Sunday the Fathers House provides Sunday Supper Service from 4 pm to 5:30 pm.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Everyone is welcome.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>Meals are served at The Hope Center, 1950 Kitrick Ave.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]God through the HC, serves up on average 1,886 meals a month. For .69 cents you can feed a person a hot meal at the HC. For $25 per month you can sponsor 36 meals.[/box]\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\"></p>','Dan\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','228-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 03:58:43','2014-10-28 03:58:43','',228,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/228-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(285,2,'2014-10-28 04:00:13','2014-10-28 04:00:13','&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\">  I had been attending the Serenity Recovery Group at the Nazarene church still struggling with my addiction until I learned I was pregnant.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>A year after my son was born, the City Quest Ministry came to my apartment complex giving out food and prayer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>After an accident I was in, I began to go to church with the City Quest team.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>My boyfriend and I are now attending church together and we have plans on getting married soon with the City Quest team officiating!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>City Quest</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Where saints from different organizations gather to be the hands and feet of Jesus and reach-out to those who live in apartment complexes and other isolated conditions...we meet needs and minister to those who would not normally make it to the Center.  Come join us!  Meet in the HC Food Bank Parking Lot on Thursday\'s at 3:30pm...Blessings</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]God through the HC distributes food to over 30 organizations throughout our City and Butte County. Last year God through the HC distributed a total of 284,742 lbs of food to individuals, families and organizations in need.[/box]','Toba\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','232-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 04:00:13','2014-10-28 04:00:13','',232,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/232-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(287,2,'2014-10-28 22:36:50','2014-10-29 05:36:50','<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">Danny’s story:  </span></strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\"> </span>The first time I experienced the Hope Center was through the City Quest Outreach Ministry which came and blessed our apartment complex with food, furniture and prayer.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I felt so blessed by what I was seeing and the love I felt, that I wanted to give back.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>So I began to volunteer in the City Quest Outreach Ministry visiting others in need and ministering to them each week.<span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">  </span>I have been volunteering now for three months and I am enjoying it!</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p1\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>City Quest</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"p2\">Where saints from different organizations gather to be the hands and feet of Jesus and reach-out to those who live in apartment complexes and other isolated conditions...we meet needs and minister to those who would not normally make it to the Center.  Come join us!  Meet in the HC Food Bank Parking Lot on Thursday\'s at 3:30pm...Blessings</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<p class=\"p2\" style=\"text-align: center;\">[button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/monthly-donation/\"] Monthly Donations[/button] [button link=\"http://orovillehopecenter.org/one-time-donation/\"] One-Time Donation[/button][button link=\" http://orovillehopecenter.org/s-h-a-r-e-s-program/\" color=\"orange\"] S.H.A.R.E.S. Card[/button]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n[box]God through the HC, serves up on average 1,886 meals a month. For .69 cents you can feed a person a hot meal at the HC. For $25 per month you can sponsor 36 meals.[/box]','Danny\'s Story','','inherit','open','open','','206-revision-v1','','','2014-10-28 22:36:50','2014-10-29 05:36:50','',206,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/206-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(289,2,'2014-11-02 16:34:32','2014-11-02 23:34:32','<p>Your Name (required)<br />\r\n    [text* your-name] </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Your Email (required)<br />\r\n    [email* your-e