INSERT INTO `old_posts` VALUES (50,1,'2011-03-31 12:49:47','2011-03-31 19:49:47','<div class=\"intro-box group\"><span class=\"heading\">Give</span>\r\n<h3 class=\"intro\">\r\nWe cannot continue our service without the financial support of generous donors. Consider a tax-deductible donation today.\r\n</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nSupport the Hope Center\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Deliver / mail a check or money order to the Hope Center</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Donate belongings to Grandma\'s Mission of Hope Thrift Shoppe</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Coming soon: donate online via PayPal</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nHayden Ministries has been privileged to have a steady and growing base of private financial supporters.  These include local citizens who understand and appreciate the mission and ministry of The Hope Center, as well as local businesses and churches longing to see lasting and impactive change in the Oroville Area.  Once we moved into our new facility, our expenses almost tripled.  Thankfully, as we have grown, our support base has grown.  But there is still room for increase, as we are almost barely able to meet all of the necessary expenses.\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\nThis is why we will be establishing a comprehensive fundraising plan, which begins with the formation of a fundraising team.  This team will be comprised of people who will oversee, coordinate and implement fundraising strategies, such as special events, campaigns by mail, online, and through local media such as television and news publication.  They will also search for grant opportunities and maintain current grant submissions and applications.  This team will be intimately involved with all facets of Hayden Ministries in order to present a current picture of our status.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n','Give','','inherit','open','open','','22-revision-4','','','2011-03-31 12:49:47','2011-03-31 19:49:47','',22,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/2011/03/22-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),(61,1,'2011-12-07 15:02:40','2011-12-07 23:02:40','<p>A Simple Gesture is a door-to-door food collection program. Check out <a href=\"http://www.asimplegesture.org/\">A Simple Gesture in Paradise</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is all you have to do:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fill out the form below.</li>\r\n    	<li>We will bring a cool, green bag to your house.  The tag hanging on the straps tell you when the pick-ups are for the year and what foods are best to buy.</li>\r\n    	<li>Each week when you go shopping buy one extra non-perishable food item.  Store it in the cool, green bag.</li>\r\n    	<li>A week before pickup we will send you an email or post card telling you to place the bag outside on the pick-up date.</li>\r\n    	<li>We will come by in the morning, pick up the bag, and leave another cool, green bag in its place.</li>\r\n    	<li>Your bag will be taken and that same day will be placed in area food pantries.</li>\r\n    	<li>If you won’t be home just call us at (530) 538-8393; we’ll arrange to pick up your food the next week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n[contact-form-7 id=\"62\"]\r\n\r\n<h3>Other Services in our Area</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Hope on the Hill</strong><br />\r\nMountain Chapel in Berry Creek<br />\r\n(530) 632-2191 or (530) 589-4655</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Plentiful Harvest Food Pantry</strong><br />\r\nCalvary Chapel, Concow<br />\r\n<a href=\"mailto:plentifulharvest@yahoo.com\">plentifulharvest@yahoo.com</a><br />\r\n(530) 533-7316</p>','A Simple Gesture','','publish','open','open','','a-simple-gesture','','','2012-01-27 13:15:17','2012-01-27 21:15:17','',22,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?page_id=61',0,'page','',0),(4,1,'2011-03-15 16:12:56','2011-03-15 23:12:56','<div class=\"intro-box group\"><span class=\"heading\">Learn</span>\r\n<h3 class=\"intro\">\r\nWe are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities.\r\n</h3>\r\n<a href=\"#services\" class=\"more\">Learn more<br />&amp; get help &darr;</a>\r\n<p>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"events\">\r\n<span class=\"subheading\">Upcoming Events</span>\r\n[google-calendar-events type=\"list\" max=\"10\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"services\">\r\n<a name=\"services\"></a>\r\n<a href=\"/give/a-simple-gesture\" title=\"Click for more info\">\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>A Simple Gesture</h3>\r\n<p>We drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to food banks around Oroville. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need? Click for more info and to sign up!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</a>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Operation Hope - Food Ministry</h3>\r\n<p>The Operation Hope team meets at 6 AM on Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday mornings to prepare and package a fresh hot breakfast for those who are hungry. The breakfast is then served at local parks in Downtown Oroville. In addition, a hot lunch is served on Fridays at The Hope Center. Everyone is welcome.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>\r\nClothing Assistance\r\n</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nOur warehouse contains organized racks of like-new clothing that are completely FREE to anyone in need.  Clients may take:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>3 bottoms</span></li>\r\n<li><span>4 tops</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 jacket</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 coat in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n<li><span>2 miscellaneous items (such as shoes, underwear, belts, etc.)</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 pajama set</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 sheet set</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 blanket in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Businesswear/suits available in addition to regular allowances for interviews, court, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul> Occasionally furniture, toiletries, hygiene products and household linens are available as well.  Clients can return once every two months for more clothing assistance, or if homeless, once every month. \r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>\r\nDay Use Center\r\n</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nAt The Hope Center, a wet-weather, drop-in, day-use center is currently under construction.  We currently serve hot meals and fellowship with the needy and homeless in our main warehouse that has a makeshift dining area and houses our Community Kitchen Trailer. We offer laundry services to homeless only Tuesday through Friday from 10am to 1pm. Showers available Tuesday through Thursday 9am to 1pm, and 11am to 1pm on Fridays.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>\r\nLife Skills Academy (LSA)\r\n</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nLife Skills Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, local government agencies, and churches to provide free basic life skills education in order to effect a positive change in peoples\' lives, helping them to contribute to the community, creating a better environment for individuals, businesses and law enforcement personnel, and even saving tax-payer dollars.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Home','','publish','open','closed','','home','','','2012-05-10 10:43:37','2012-05-10 17:43:37','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?page_id=4',1,'page','',0),(5,1,'2011-03-15 16:12:52','2011-03-15 23:12:52','','Auto Draft','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision','','','2011-03-15 16:12:52','2011-03-15 23:12:52','',4,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/2011/03/4-revision/',0,'revision','',0),(6,1,'2011-03-15 16:13:02','2011-03-15 23:13:02','','Learn','','publish','open','closed','','learn','','','2011-03-15 16:14:42','2011-03-15 23:14:42','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?page_id=6',2,'page','',0),(7,1,'2011-03-15 16:12:58','2011-03-15 23:12:58','','Auto Draft','','inheri