nav_menu_item','',0),(29,1,'2011-03-16 10:38:41','2011-03-16 17:38:41',' ','','','publish','open','open','','29','','','2011-03-16 10:43:10','2011-03-16 17:43:10','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=29',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(30,1,'2011-03-16 10:38:41','2011-03-16 17:38:41',' ','','','publish','open','open','','30','','','2011-03-16 10:43:10','2011-03-16 17:43:10','',0,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/?p=30',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(31,1,'2011-03-15 16:48:40','2011-03-15 23:48:40','Something','Home','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-5','','','2011-03-15 16:48:40','2011-03-15 23:48:40','',4,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/2011/03/4-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),(34,1,'2011-03-31 10:30:38','2011-03-31 17:30:38','Welcome to the THE HOPE CENTER, a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities, offering emergency food and clothing assistance as well as counseling and education programs that provide essential and fundamental life resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty.','Home','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-7','','','2011-03-31 10:30:38','2011-03-31 17:30:38','',4,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/2011/03/4-revision-7/',0,'revision','',0),(32,1,'2012-05-10 10:42:14','2012-05-10 17:42:14','<div class=\"intro-box group\"><span class=\"heading\">Learn</span>\r\n<h3 class=\"intro\">\r\nWe are a non-profit Christian outreach that ministers to Butte County and the surrounding communities.\r\n</h3>\r\n<a href=\"#services\" class=\"more\">Learn more<br />&amp; get help &darr;</a>\r\n<p>\r\nWe offer\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>Emergency food and clothing</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Counseling and education programs</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Resources to families who are battling many kinds of poverty</span></li>\r\n<li><span>We are closed every 2<sup>nd</sup> week of the month, and every 2<sup>nd</sup> Thursday is commodities queue until done</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"events\">\r\n<span class=\"subheading\">Upcoming Events</span>\r\n[google-calendar-events type=\"list\" max=\"10\"]\r\n</div>\r\n<div id=\"services\">\r\n<a name=\"services\"></a>\r\n<a href=\"/give/a-simple-gesture\" title=\"Click for more info\">\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>A Simple Gesture</h3>\r\n<p>We drop off a shopping bag to your doorstep. Over the course of 2 months, you fill it with items listed on the tag. We pick it up and deliver the food to food banks around Oroville. What could be a simpler way to give to those in need? Click for more info and to sign up!</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</a>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>Operation Hope - Food Ministry</h3>\r\n<p>The Operation Hope team meets at 6 AM on Tuesday, Thursday and Saturday mornings to prepare and package a fresh hot breakfast for those who are hungry. The breakfast is then served at local parks in Downtown Oroville. In addition, a hot lunch is served on Fridays at The Hope Center. Everyone is welcome.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>\r\nClothing Assistance\r\n</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nOur warehouse contains organized racks of like-new clothing that are completely FREE to anyone in need.  Clients may take:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span>3 bottoms</span></li>\r\n<li><span>4 tops</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 jacket</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 coat in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n<li><span>2 miscellaneous items (such as shoes, underwear, belts, etc.)</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 pajama set</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 sheet set</span></li>\r\n<li><span>1 blanket in a 6 month period</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Businesswear/suits available in addition to regular allowances for interviews, court, etc.</span></li>\r\n</ul> Occasionally furniture, toiletries, hygiene products and household linens are available as well.  Clients can return once every two months for more clothing assistance, or if homeless, once every month. \r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>\r\nDay Use Center\r\n</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nAt The Hope Center, a wet-weather, drop-in, day-use center is currently under construction.  We currently serve hot meals and fellowship with the needy and homeless in our main warehouse that has a makeshift dining area and houses our Community Kitchen Trailer. We offer laundry services to homeless only Tuesday through Friday from 10am to 1pm.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"box group\">\r\n<h3>\r\nLife Skills Academy (LSA)\r\n</h3>\r\n<p>\r\nLife Skills Academy is a collaboration that includes The Hope Center, local government agencies, and churches to provide free basic life skills education in order to effect a positive change in peoples\' lives, helping them to contribute to the community, creating a better environment for individuals, businesses and law enforcement personnel, and even saving tax-payer dollars.\r\n</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>','Home','','inherit','open','open','','4-autosave','','','2012-05-10 10:42:14','2012-05-10 17:42:14','',4,'http://orovillehopecenter.org/2011/03/4-autosave/',0,'revision','',0),(33,1,'2011-03-16 11:10:39','2011-03-16 18:10:39','Nunc mi mi, scelerisque sit amet varius sit amet, auctor vel leo. Duis gravida odio et est pellentesque malesuada. Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. In id mollis ligula. In hac habitasse platea dictumst. Etiam aliquet ultrices ligula ut egestas. Duis tortor lectus, commodo sed rhoncus vel, molestie molestie velit. Etiam velit augue, tincidunt ut tincidunt non, sollicitudin quis dui. Nulla facilisi. Nam elementum lobortis felis, id mattis orci placerat at. Quisque convallis, ipsum ac gravida gravida, est erat gravida nunc, nec tincidunt arcu nunc molestie quam. Suspendisse ultricies eros id velit malesuada faucibus. Sed condimentum condimentum tempus. Nunc ac lacus commodo tortor porta tincidunt ac et justo. Etiam magna nisi, porttitor ut semper at, condimentum non est. Donec et nisl eu massa aliquam euismod. Sed sagittis gravida sapien, molestie facilisis ligula consectetur non. ','Ho